# Explainable Code Plagiarism Detection

This project is a full-stack app for plagiarism detection in code submissions.

It lets instructors:
- create collections and datasets
- upload ZIP files of student code
- run an analysis job
- track progress by stages
- review pair similarity results
- open side-by-side file comparison

## Tech Stack

### Backend
- Python 3.12+
- FastAPI
- SQLAlchemy
- Pydantic
- Celery
- Uvicorn

### Frontend
- React (Vite)
- TypeScript
- npm

## Project Structure

- `backend/`: API, models, job pipeline, database logic
- `frontend/`: React UI and API client helpers
- `DamiReadme`: This project summary and progress log

## How To Run (Recommended For Team And Demo)

Use Docker Compose so every teammate can run the exact same stack with one command.

### 1. Prerequisites

- Install Docker Desktop
- Start Docker Desktop and wait until it is running

Optional checks:

```powershell
docker --version
docker compose version
```

### 2. Start everything

From project root:

```powershell
docker compose up --build
```

This starts:
- frontend (Vite)
- backend (FastAPI)
- celery worker
- redis
- postgres

### 3. Open the app

- Frontend: http://localhost:5173
- Backend health: http://localhost:8000/api/health
- Backend docs: http://localhost:8000/docs

### 4. Stop services

In the same terminal, press Ctrl + C, then run:

```powershell
docker compose down
```

### 5. Clean reset (if needed)

```powershell
docker compose down -v
docker compose up --build
```

