## Learning Notes

This codebase is currently structured so each part is easy to follow:
- API layer handles HTTP requests.
- Job layer handles stage processing.
- UI layer polls status and displays results.

The TOKENS and AST algorithm logic can be plugged in later without changing the overall app flow.

## How file uploads work
You pick a collection.
You upload one ZIP as a dataset.
Each top-level folder (Alice, Rob) becomes one submission/student.
Code files inside each folder are read and saved in the database.
Later, when you click Run Plagiarism Detection, the system compares files from those submissions.